Sentencas: In this research, the performance of a tubular fuel cell based on a nickel oxide-yttria-stabilized zirconia (Ni-YSZ) anode support containing 90 wt% NiO approximate to 82 vol.% of Ni (Ni82) is compared with a cell containing the conventional Ni-YSZ support with 50 vol.% Ni.
Titulo: Tailoring the solid oxide fuel cell anode support composition and microstructure for low-temperature applications

Sentencas: A Ni-YSZ buffer layer with a tailored microstructure was added to the Ni82 support layer to provide intermediate porosity and to reduce the thermal expansion mismatch with the anode functional layer.
Titulo: Tailoring the solid oxide fuel cell anode support composition and microstructure for low-temperature applications

Sentencas: Both cells were tested using infiltrated Nd2NiO4+delta cathodes.
Titulo: Tailoring the solid oxide fuel cell anode support composition and microstructure for low-temperature applications

Sentencas: High peak power densities of 790 and 478 mW/cm(2) were achieved at 600 and 550 degrees C, respectively, for the Ni82 cell which was 25% and 87% higher than the performances for the conventional cell at respective temperatures.
Titulo: Tailoring the solid oxide fuel cell anode support composition and microstructure for low-temperature applications

Sentencas: In addition, no degradation was found during four redox cycles at 550 degrees C, making this support an attractive candidate for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell applications.
Titulo: Tailoring the solid oxide fuel cell anode support composition and microstructure for low-temperature applications
